---
title: Hoisin Beef & Cabbage with Jasmine Rice & Sriracha
description: This saucy, sweet, and spicy dish is ready in just 20 minutes—that’s faster than takes to order delivery! Ground beef is browned with cabbage, carrots, onion, and scallions, then tossed in a blend of sweet soy glaze and tangy hoisin sauce. It’s all spooned over buttery jasmine rice and garnished with Sriracha for customizable heat. Talk about a dinner dream come true!
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/hoisin-beef-cabbage-eb0c1e2e.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/hoisin-beef-cabbage-60e5b8ada698f845611d5f06-604bca64.pdf
course: main course
cuisine: Asian
servings: 2
time required: 20 minutes
author: Michelle Doll Olson
nutrition:
  calories: 830 kcal
  fat: 31 g
  saturated fat: 13 g
  carbohydrates: 104 g
  sugar: 30 g
  protein: 30 g
  fiber: 4 g
  sodium: 1800 mg
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/hoisin-beef-cabbage-60e5b8ada698f845611d5f06
---

In a small #pot{}, combine @jasmine rice{3/4%cup}, 1¼ cups water, and a pinch of
@salt{pinch}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook
until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

While rice cooks, wash and dry produce.

Halve, peel, and thinly slice @yellow onion{1}(peeled and thinly sliced). Peel and
mince or grate @ginger{1%thumb}(minced). Trim and thinly slice
@scallions{2}(trimmed and thinly sliced), separating whites from greens.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tsp} in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add
onion and ginger; season lightly with @salt{}. Cook, stirring occasionally,
until softened, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Add @ground beef{10%ounce} and cook, breaking up meat into pieces, until
browned, ~{3-5%minutes}. TIP: If there's excess grease in your pan, carefully
pour it out.

Stir in scallion whites, @shredded red cabbage{4%ounce}, and
@shredded carrots{4%ounce}. Cook, stirring occasionally, until veggies are
softened and beef is cooked through, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Stir in @hoisin sauce{4%tablespoon}, @soy sauce{2%tablespoon}, half the
@rice wine vinegar{5%teaspoon}, and @sugar{1/2%teaspoon}. Cook for ~{1%minute}
more.

Turn off heat.

Fluff rice with a #fork{} and stir in @butter{1%tablespoon}; season with salt and
@pepper{}.

Divide rice between bowls and top with beef mixture. Drizzle with
@sriracha{1%teaspoon} to taste and sprinkle with scallion greens. Serve.

> This saucy, sweet, and spicy dish is ready in just 20 minutes—that's faster
> than it takes to order delivery! Ground beef is browned with cabbage,
> carrots, onion, and scallions, then tossed in a blend of sweet soy glaze
> and tangy hoisin sauce. It's all spooned over buttery jasmine rice and
> garnished with Sriracha for customizable heat. Talk about a dinner dream
> come true!